'''Azzopardi''' is a [[Malta|Maltese]] [[surname]] derived from ''A Safardi'', which means "A Jew coming from [[Spain]]". Most of the Azzopardi families in Malta originated in Toledano, [[Spain]].

Though Jewish in origin, most of the families converted to [[Catholicism]] in [[1492]] when the Jews were expelled from Malta, while those that refused had to leave the Islands. A few of the families that remained are known to have practised Judaism in secret, but these families eventually converted fully to Catholicism.

'''Azzopardi''' may refer to:

*[[Mario Azzopardi]], Maltese film director
*[[Peppi Azzopardi]], [[television|TV]] presenter of shows such as [http://www.xarabank.com Xarabank] and programmes.
*[[Stephen Azzopardi]], contemporary Maltese artist ([http://www.stephenazzopardi.com official website])

